item.description:
Because I can, I created a diagram generator for Homeworlds. For now, it&apos;s available here: https://www.abstractplay.com/_tools/renderer/homeworlds.html. It takes text input like the following and produces the SVG. Maybe this will be useful to someone out there. If so, let me know and I&apos;ll refine it further.
```json
{
    &quot;numPlayers&quot;: 2,
    &quot;universe&quot;: [
        {
            &quot;owner&quot;: &quot;N&quot;,
            &quot;stars&quot;: [&quot;G2&quot;, &quot;B1&quot;],
            &quot;ships&quot;: [&quot;Y3N&quot;]
        },
        {
            &quot;owner&quot;: &quot;S&quot;,
            &quot;stars&quot;: [&quot;G3&quot;, &quot;R1&quot;],
            &quot;ships&quot;: [&quot;B3S&quot;]
        },
        {
            &quot;stars&quot;: [&quot;R3&quot;],
            &quot;ships&quot;: [&quot;Y1N&quot;]
        }
    ]
}
```

@ypaul brings us a new bounty: - Crummack &amp; Galley&apos;s game of spreading and converting, Ataxx - Nick Bentley&apos;s game Bug - Arrausi&apos;s sowing game Buku - George S. Parker&apos;s Chess/draughts-like Camelot - Bill Taylor&apos;s game Majorities - And two new Tumbleweed variants: - &quot;Capture delay,&quot; where you may not place at where your opponent just placed, and - &quot;Free neutral,&quot; where on the first turn you place a 2-stack neutral piece and a 1-stack piece of each player&apos;s colour.
And finally, @Castux joins our group of @Code Contributors by coding his own territory-control game Tritium.
Thanks to you both! Enjoy!

More new games! Enjoy!
@ypaul brings us three new connection games: - Christian Freeling&apos;s games Query and Lox - Nick Bentley&apos;s game Shifty
And @ManaT brings us @dalewalton&apos;s first game here at AP, Natal Seas - Pods.
